--- !u!114 &456653022
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 456653021}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8629b1ed2663be048b4c0880a63a4f3a, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialoguePanel: {fileID: 885184085}
  dialogueText: {fileID: 2038864940}
  dialogue:
  - 'Innkeeper: It''s surprising to see anyone out and about tonight after what happened. '
  - 'Rosalie: I was hoping you might have an available room to rent for the night? '
  - 'Innkeeper: Sure do, there''s a cozy room just down the hall with your name on
    it. '
  - 'Rosalie: That''s great! How much would I owe you?'
  - 'Innkeeper: A single room would be 8 coins for the night. '
  - 'Rosalie: ...'
  - '*Rosalie looks in her coin pouch to find only two coins*'
  - 'Innkeeper: Don''t have enough?'
  - 'Innkeeper: Hmmm...'
  - 'Innkeeper: How about this. '
  - 'Innkeeper: I can''t kick you out in the cold, especially not this evening. '
  - 'Innkeeper: So, I''ll lower the price to 5 coins. '
  - 'Inkeeper: How''s that sound?'
  - 'Rosalie: That''s generous of you but...'
  - 'Innkeeper: Don''t worry!'
  - 'Innkeeper: If you head back into the square and walk south a little ways you''ll
    find a merchant''s house.'
  - 'Innkeeper: A good friend of mine runs the place; his name is Mand. '
  - 'Innkeeper:  He''s an older gentleman and looks kind of scary, but he has a real
    good soul. '
  - 'Innkeeper: Tell him Areli sent you.'
  - 'Areli Avhallen: He might even throw in a few extra coins if you have something
    to trade!'
  - 'Rosalie: Really!? Thanks for the directions!'
  - '*You choose to give her the outpost guard''s message*'
  - 'Rosalie: I almost forgot!'
  - 'Rosalie: I ran into your husband on my way to the village.'
  - 'Rosalie: He says not to worry, he''ll be home as soon as he can. '
  - 'Areli Avhallen: Oh Arthur...'
  - 'Areli Avhallen: Truth is I''ve been worried sick about him.'
  - 'Areli Avhallen: I can''t seem to shake the chills I got from seeing that weird
    phenomemon in the sky. '
  - 'Rosalie: I know what you mean, I still haven''t processed it myself. '
  - 'Areli Avhallen: What''s your name miss? '
  - 'Rosalie: It''s Rosalie, Rosalie Nehrai.'
  - 'Areli Avhallen: Thank you, Rosalie.'
  - 'Areli Avhallen: I needed to hear that he was okay.'
  - 'Rosalie: Of course.'
  - 'Areli Avhallen: Hurry on now!'
  - 'Areli Avhallen: I''ll have a warm mel ready for when you get back, free of charge!'
  - 'Areli Avhallen: Be careful out there. '
  index: 0
  wordSpeed: 0.05
  playerIsClose: 0
