--- !u!114 &2066907078
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 2066907077}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8629b1ed2663be048b4c0880a63a4f3a, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialoguePanel: {fileID: 435533187}
  dialogueText: {fileID: 1014356973}
  dialogue:
  - 'Rosalie: You must be Mand!'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Dependin'' on who''s askin''.'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: In any case, shop is closed for the night. Come back first
    thing in the mornin'', you could be my first customer. '
  - 'Rosalie: I don''t mean to be a bother, I was just hoping to make a quick trade
    to help pay for a room at the inn.'
  - 'Rosalie: Areli gave me a generous discount and pointed me in your direction.'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Areli huh? She''s a kind gal. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Hmm...'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Alright kid, I don''t usually do business at this hour but
    I''ll make an exception. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: What are you lookin'' to trade?'
  - '*Rosalie pulls out a necklace from her travel pack*'
  - 'Rosalie: While I was moving through the Grasslands, I found this necklace.'
  - 'Rosalie: It was laying at the foot of a large tree in a glade.'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Can''t say I''ve ever seen anything like this symbol...'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: The craftsmanship is elegant. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Found this in the Grasslands huh? '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: It''s rare but I''ve had foreign objects come through my
    shop before. This necklace looks like it could come from another land outside
    Silva Aetherea. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: But there''s also some familiar aspects to it. '
  - 'Rosalie: It was precious to somebody somewhere. '
  - 'Rosalie: I feel a bit bad selling it but...'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Won''t get any judgment from me. '
  - '*Rosalie asks about the sky phenomenon*'
  - 'Rosalie: Hey, did you see that stuff in the sky earlier?'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Was hard to miss.'
  - 'Rosalie: I wonder if it was some sort of magic...'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: I don''t think even the "great minds" of Babylon could do
    somethin'' like that.'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Not unless they found some kinda new magic stone. .'
  - 'Rosalie: If not magic, then what do you think might''ve caused it?'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Somethin'' else entirely. Looked like it all happend right
    above the forest of Silva Aetherea. '
  - '*Rosalie asks more about Silva Aetherea*'
  - 'Rosalie: Could you tell me more about Silva Aetherea?'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: From the edge of the Grasslands in the South all the way
    to the ocean in the North is considered the "The Land of Silva Aetherea". '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: It''s one giant forest, full of all kinds of history. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: The oldest civilization we know of in these lands called
    it home thousands of years ago. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: They''re the onse that named it. '
  - 'Rosalie: "Silva Aetherea"...what does it mean? '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: "Ethereal Forest"'
  - 'Rosalie: Ethereal?'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: It''s said the people of that civilization almost worshipped
    the forest. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Couldn''t tell you why. You''d have to ask some historian
    or somethin''.'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: What I can tell you is this...'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: When there''s no one else around, and you''re standin'' deep
    in the forest...'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: There''s a sort of presence you start to feel.'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: You''re head tells you you''re all alone, but your senses
    tell you you''re surrounded by somethin'' just out of view. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: If you''re plannin'' on going through there soon, be careful.
    ''Specially with that sky nonsense earlier. '
  - 'Rosalie: Thanks, I''ll keep that in mind. '
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Anyway, you should get goin'' soon, it''s gettin'' real late.'
  - 'Rosalie: You''re right, don''t want to keep Areli waiting too long. Thanks for
    the help sir!'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Call me Mand kid, and no problem.'
  - 'Mand the Merchant: Give Areli my best regards. '
  - '*Mand the Merchant pays Rosalie for the unique necklace with a few extra coins
    on top*'
  index: 0
  wordSpeed: 0.05
  playerIsClose: 0
